data.message:
I haven't played a lot with it, but I made a small game with MonoGame framework (XNA port) and I used Xamarin Trial and it worked great.
@Marwan Atef: It compiles C# to IL (like the Microsoft's compiler) then for iOS then do some Ahead-of-Time compilation to iOS Native, and for Android they package Mono's runtime (interpreter) with your app's IL (that's why the APK is huge).
The Xamarin guys claim that C# runs faster than Java on Android in many cases, and they actually tried porting some parts of Android from Java to C# and it worked faster :D
